1338","1367":"1367","1378":"1378","Abt 1320":"about 1320","1320":"1320","1393":"1393","England":"England","Malton, York, England":"Malton, Yorkshire, England, United Kingdom","nameMeanings":[{"name":"Grey","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["English, Scottish, and Irish: variant of   Gray  .","German: dialect variant of   Grau  .","In some cases also an American shortened and altered form of Ukrainian <b>Grushko</b>: nickname or topographic name derived from a Russian-influenced transliteration of <i>grushka</i> ‘pear, pear tree’."],"variants":[{"name":"Gray","meanings":["English, Scottish, and Irish (especially Eastern Ulster; of Norman origin): habitational name from Graye in Calvados, France, named from the Gallo-Roman personal name <i>Graec(i)us</i>, meaning ‘Greek’ + the locative suffix <i>-acum</i>. This is probably the chief source of the surname in Britain.","English: nickname for someone with gray hair or a gray beard, from Middle English <i>grey</i> (Old English <i>grǣg</i>, <i>grēg</i>) ‘gray’. In Ireland it has been used as a translation of various Gaelic surnames derived from <i>riabhach</i> ‘brindled, gray’, including <b>Mac Giolla Riabhaigh</b>; see   McGreevy  . In North America, this surname has assimilated names with similar meaning from other languages.","French: habitational name from Gray in Haute-Saône or Le Gray in Seine-Maritime."]},{"name":"Greiwe","meanings":["German: possibly a nickname from Middle High German <i>greibe</i> ‘sharp, tangy, dour’. Compare   Grey  ."]}]},{"name":"Margaret","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["An extremely common given name from the Middle Ages onwards, derived via Old French <i>Marguerite</i> and Latin <i>Margarita</i> from Greek <i>Margarītēs</i>, from <i>margaron</i> ‘pearl’, a word ultimately of Hebrew origin. The name was always understood to mean ‘pearl’ throughout the Middle Ages. The first  St Margaret  was martyred at Antioch in Pisidia during the persecution instigated by the  Emperor Diocletian  in the early 4th century. However, there is some doubt about her name, as the same saint is venerated in the Orthodox Church as   Marina .  There were several other saintly bearers of the name, including St Margaret of Scotland (  d. 1093 ), wife of  King Malcolm Canmore  and daughter of Edmund Ironside of England. It was also the name of the wife of  Henry VI  of England,  Margaret of Anjou  (  1430–82 ), and of  Margaret Tudor  (  1489–1541 ), sister of  Henry VIII , who married James IV of Scotland and ruled as regent there after his death.  See also  Margery  ,   Marjorie ."],"variants":[{"name":"Margareta","meanings":["From the Latin form of Greek <i>Margarītēs</i>.  See  <b>Margaret</b>   ."]},{"name":"Margaretta","meanings":["An extremely common given name from the Middle Ages onwards, derived via Old French <i>Marguerite</i> and Latin <i>Margarita</i> from Greek <i>Margarītēs</i>, from <i>margaron</i> ‘pearl’, a word ultimately of Hebrew origin. The name was always understood to mean ‘pearl’ throughout the Middle Ages. The first  St Margaret  was martyred at Antioch in Pisidia during the persecution instigated by the  Emperor Diocletian  in the early 4th century. However, there is some doubt about her name, as the same saint is venerated in the Orthodox Church as   Marina .  There were several other saintly bearers of the name, including St Margaret of Scotland (  d. 1093 ), wife of  King Malcolm Canmore  and daughter of Edmund Ironside of England. It was also the name of the wife of  Henry VI  of England,  Margaret of Anjou  (  1430–82 ), and of  Margaret Tudor  (  1489–1541 ), sister of  Henry VIII , who married James IV of Scotland and ruled as regent there after his death.  See also  Margery  ,   Marjorie ."]}]}],"lifeSummary":"Margaret Grey was born about 1320, in Malton, Yorkshire, England, United Kingdom. She married John Eure. They were the parents of at least 1 son. She died in 1378, at the age of 59."},"et":{"Abt 1320–1378":"umbes 1320–1378","1303–1367":"1303–1367","1338–1393":"1338–1393","1320–1378":"1320–1378","1338":"1338","1303":"1303","abt 1338":"umbes 1338","1367":"1367","1378":"1378","Abt 1320":"umbes 1320","1320":"1320","1393":"1393","England":"England","Malton, York, England":"Malton, Yorkshire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom"},"fi":{"Abt 1320–1378":"noin 1320–1378","1303–1367":"1303–1367","1338–1393":"1338–1393","1320–1378":"1320–1378","1338":"1338","1303":"1303","abt 1338":"noin 1338","1367":"1367","1378":"1378","Abt 1320":"noin 1320","1320":"1320","1393":"1393","England":"England","Malton, York, England":"Malton, Yorkshire, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta"},"fr":{"Abt 1320–1378":"environ 1320–1378","1303–1367":"1303–1367","1338–1393":"1338–1393","1320–1378":"1320–1378","1338":"1338","1303":"1303","abt 1338":"environ 1338","1367":"1367","1378":"1378","Abt 1320":"environ 1320","1320":"1320","1393":"1393","England":"Angleterre","Malton, York, England":"Malton, Everwyck, Angleterre, Royaume-Uni","lifeSummary":"Margaret Grey est née environ 1320, à Malton, Everwyck, Angleterre, Royaume-Uni. Elle a épousé John Eure. Ils ont eu au moins 1 fils. Elle est décédée en 1378, à l’âge de 59 ans."},"de":{"Abt 1320–1378":"um 1320–1378","1303–1367":"1303–1367","1338–1393":"1338–1393","1320–1378":"1320–1378","1338":"1338","1303":"1303","abt 1338":"um 1338","1367":"1367","1378":"1378","Abt 1320":"um 1320","1320":"1320","1393":"1393","England":"England","Malton, York, England":"Malton, Yorkshire, England, United Kingdom","lifeSummary":"Margaret Grey wurde um 1320 in Malton, Yorkshire, England, United Kingdom geboren. Sie hat John Eure geheiratet. Sie hatten mindestens 1 Sohn. Sie starb 1378 im Alter von 59 Jahren."},"ht":{"Abt 1320–1378":"about 1320–1378","1303–1367":"1303–1367","1338–1393":"1338–1393","1320–1378":"1320–1378","1338":"1338","1303":"1303","abt 1338":"abo